column5: Finally took a morning to hook up on some silvers this morning.  Did not take long to hook up on the fresh run. All on Cleardrift, peach/orange 8mm bead. Already in the brine to smoke up tomorrow.
You ever cut them open and see what they have been eating. I know not much but there could be a small fish in there.
Never looked. I slice ,see nice red meat and say,SMOKER TIME.
Nice man!!!  I need to get out there soon.
Great morning went bad for my fishing buddy.  Got rammed. He is fine,but SUV and trailer and craft not.
What a sad sight.  People seem to tailgate when you’re towing.
At least its' last trip resulted in some nice fish. Sorry to see that happen.
Well as long as your bud is ok, that's # 1.  Far too many idiots on the road nowadays.  Everyone needs a dashcam and one for the back.
The first of the season is da best bye. Drizzled some maple syrup on them. Sweet and salty.

Looks awesome...I do a half maple syrup, half whiskey drizzle as they smoke.. I thought the season has been going strong since April...lol. Good year on G Bay this summer...nice to see the numbers bounce back. The tourney had over 1500 fish entered this year.
Well,I am a river rat guy,so wait time is different. Good early numbers swimming up already here. Giving it another go in the AM.

They've started on Lake O too....already over 700 have passed through Corbett's. They always start early up your way. I remember back in 2012 we were getting chrome Chinnies at Montgomery's in July...that was a weird year. Best of luck tomorrow..Get 'em while they're fresh !
﻿ Stay where you're to 'till I comes where you're at.
